EmailTemplate.name: DR 2013 - Week 1 Final Email
EmailTemplate.subject: DR #1 - Final Email
EmailTemplate.textOnly:
Hello Live Different Build Volunteers!
Wow, can you believe we will be in the Dominican Republic soon? I hope you are all as excited as I am to meet all of the amazing people we will be working alongside!
Some final information and reminders...(lots of important information below, please take the time to read it thoroughly!)
1. FLIGHTS As of June 1st, if you are flying to Toronto everyone should have forwarded their flight itineraries to me. If you have not forwarded your flight itinerary, you need to do that as soon as possible. We want to make sure that a Live Different representative is waiting at the airport to meet you when you come out of the security area. Our representative will be holding a BIG sign that says, "Live Different Build".
2. PASSPORTS Please bring 2 photocopies of your passport with you. One will be handed into me upon registration on your first day, and the other is for you to keep on yourself. This is a precaution just in case your passport goes missing while travelling. Double check before you leave your driveway that you have your passport with you. You must have a valid passport to travel with us to Dominican Republic. If at the time of applying for your trip you did not have a passport and you have not emailed me your passport number, then please send that number to me immediately, along with your passport expiry date.
3. CHECKED BAGGAGE Also, remember only ONE checked bag, one carry-on bag, and a purse or laptop/camera bag can fly with you. Your checked bag cannot weigh more then 50lbs. There is also an additional cost for this check bag ($25 USD) that you will need to cover for your flight to Puerto Plata on July 3rd. Please have this ready to hand in at registration on July 2nd so that we can pay for the group as one lump sum at the ticketing counter when we depart on July 3rd.
4. EXCURSIONS There are some excursions being offered on your day off - and they are a blast! Activities will be explained and announced on your first night in Dominican Republic, the costs of full day excursion are generally between $60-90 USD.
5. EMERGENCY CONTACTS The best way to get in touch with us during airport pick-ups and registration in Canada is: Joy Yu (this is my cell phone number) - 905-746-0698, I will not be in the office on the day of bus shuttle pick ups.
If your family needs to contact you in case of emergency while in Dominican Republic, these are the numbers to call. Live Different Office (Canada) - 1-866-432-4464
Emergency 24 hour number (Dominican Repubilic): Kelly (Emergency Contact) - 809 991 2043 Kent - 809 991 2661
Sosua by the Sea front des - 1-809-571-3222. Please either leave a message or ask for the Live Different Build office/Joy Yu/Kelly Fearon (111) or your son or daughter's room number if you know it.
For general inquiries and non-urgent matters, please contact us via email joy@livedifferent. Emails are checked regularly throughout the day and someone will be scheduled in the office from 8am - 5pm EST. Someone will be available to answer the emergency phone number 24 hours/day.
6. PHONE AND INTERNET ACCESS Calling cards do not often work in the DR as 1-800 are not collect and will cost you money to call. Some past participants have put international plans on their cell phones prior to leaving but you will need to contact your cell service provider to see if this is possible. There is a internet cafe and wifi available for purchase at the resort and you can use skype to call family as well. The internet minute prices for wireless and the cafe are approximately $2 for an hour, $5 for a day, $25 for the week (USD). Some people like to bring their laptops as well, but keep in mind that Live Different is not responsible for lost or stolen items. There are safes available in the rooms for smaller valuable items, but they are not large enough to fit most laptops.
7. IMPORTANT! TRAVEL CONSENT FORMS FOR MINORS Travel Consent forms for all minors (anyone under 18 years at the time of the Live Different Build). We will be traveling into the US via a connecting flight on our way to Puerto Plata. To avoid all issues with US customs we need to make sure we are traveling with all documents needed. We ask that all minors hand in the form attached to this e-mail. I have filled out some of the information for you.
PARENTS: You must fill this form out for your child. Please hand this form in upon registration, as we need original signatures for travel.
8. IN THEIR SHOES EXPERIENCE This summer you will have a chance to participate in one of the most impacting experiences that our Live Different Build trips have to offer called, "In Their Shoes". This is our Garbage Dump work day (1/2 day max). Please remember to pack longer light-weight pants, 2 pairs of leather work gloves, a hat, and closed-toe shoes for this day (running shoes are acceptable, or if you have room, rubber boots).
9. EXTRA NIGHT If you are planning to stay overnight at the Travelodge on July 12th, please bring your payment with you to registration. The cost (per person) for this room is $30 for a quad room (4 people), $60 for a double room (2 people), and $120 for a private room (just you!).
10. SPENDING MONEY/CURRENCY It is best to bring USD cash with you, CDN cash will also be accepted. If you choose to purchase an excursion on your day off, the only other things you will need to pay for with your spending money is:
*Your meals while traveling to and from Toronto and in transit to and from Dominican Republic. *Any personal spending, souvenirs, or snacks purchased at the store. *$30 USD Resort staff tip ($60 for summer interns). *$20 USD for a night out for dinner in a fun beach town with your team.
11. PROJECT PAGE We have set up a project page which will be updated daily: http://livedifferent.com/hero-holiday/trips/public-trip-1-dr-2013 On this trip page, under the "PROJECT" tab, will be where your family and friends can see daily updates, links to the photos on our Live Different facebook page, and the trip blogs, (look out, I may be asking you to help me write a blog...volunteers needed!!) Once your trip has started, feel free to tell your friends and family to check this page out daily, (hint, if you email this link to them or post it on your facebook, it's a lot easier for them to find it!). We do our best to post a blog everyday but sometimes there are issues with the resort's internet.
12. PACKING LIST A packing list is attached for all who need it again. One great thing to pack that is not on the list is Gatorade mix for your water, which helps to replenish your electrolytes after working hard in the hot sun! Sanitizer wipes are also pretty handy to have before you eat your packed lunches too. Don't forget BUG SPRAY!!!
13. FAMILY PROFILES Projects and families have been decided and photos and bios will be up by next Monday! I will send another e-mail out once this is up.
Please feel free to email me with any of your questions,
See you soon!
